==English==
===Verb===
{{en-verb|predominat|ing}}
#{{italbrac|intransitive}} To [[dominate]], have [[control]], or succeed by superior numbers or size.
#{{italbrac|intransitive}} To be prominent; to loom large; to be the chief component of a whole.
#{{italbrac|transitive}} To dominate or hold power over, especially through numerical advantage; to outweigh.

